quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  55,46,"A twin garden (in paradise) exists (as a reward) for the one who dreads to stand before his Lord, (and His reckoning)"
  55,47,"So, which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)"
  55,48,With diverse wondrous things (in each)
  55,49,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,50,With a couple of springs streaming across each (garden)
  55,51,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,52,With two varieties of each type of fruit in each (garden)
  55,53,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,54,"(The righteous) would recline on (exotic) carpets lined with lush brocade. (Loaded with plentiful fruit), the branches of fruit trees would hang low, within easy reach"
  55,55,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,56,"In these (gardens of paradise), the righteous shall have mates that are chaste-eyed and demure _ not deflowered by any human or jinn before them"
  55,57,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,58,"(So very lovely), as if they were rubies and pearls"
  55,59,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,60,Do excellent deeds deserve anything except the most excellent rewards
  55,61,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,62,"In addition to the two (already promised), they shall have two more gardens"
  55,63,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,64,(With foliage) of the deepest green color
  55,65,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,66,With two (constantly) gushing fountains in each (garden)
  55,67,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,68,Each with (plenty of) fruits _ dates and pomegranates
  55,69,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,70,"There, they shall have beautiful virtuous (wives)"
  55,71,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,72,Lovely eyed (heavenly) nymphs (of paradise) lodged in pavilions
  55,73,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,74,Whom no human or jinn had deflowered
  55,75,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,76,"The righteous shall recline on lush green cushion, and exquisite (exotic) carpet"
  55,77,So which one of the favors of your Lord won´t you acknowledge? (For how long)
  55,78,"Hallowed is the name of your Lord, the Lord of Might and Majesty"